Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)
Date: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 2 May 2023
ReviewText: I work as a gardener and for 7 years have been using Tozo in ears. I didn't want to spend a lot as items get wet/muddy and lost but finally decided to get the Pixel A Series and WOW...first of all they are extremely comfortable (compared with the various Tozo ones) and they sound brilliant and very light in weight, you can change bass etc (well on my pixel phone)They connect as soon as taken out the box and discount when you put them back in (including if you want to take just one out)They also read out messages and alerts if you hold down the touch button on the buds (including reading whatsapp messages) and you can reply and use Google assistant to ask questions.For me they are just brilliant and couldn't recommend enough.Well done Google team.

Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)
ReviewText: A very good product and value for money.  Its connection to various gadgets such as anodrid phone, iPhone, Tablet and Apple TV are seamless and very fast. The battery also last long for my more than an hour long walk. very light weight and fit into the ears so nicely. At times don't even feel it. As I am mostly using for hearing talks and not music, I don't care about the sound control and bass etc. Touch control also fine. I have not yet used for calls on the roads.

Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)
ReviewText: Amidst push for higher version, budget was a huge constraint and I Purchased this A-series buds with two minds.But now having experienced it .. I am blown away by the sheer quality of this buds. It absolutely music to ears. Works flawlessly.. when taken out of case, it connects to phone in an instant.Sound quality is just superb.100% satisfied with this buds.Thank you Google for engineering such genuine and honest products that just mind blowing with no compromise in quality.

Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)
ReviewText: Out of the box,  it paired straight away with my google pixel,  no complications encountered.The music playback was very decent,  much better than my old creative outliers.The noise cancelling was also very good, managed to hold a teleconversation in an outdoor environment (coffee shop) with no problems.

Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)
Date: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 22 July 2023
ReviewText: Got these on prime day, so decent price. I just wanted them for use at work to listen to music while plodding on. But I've found them great for several uses. They are now always used when driving motorbike, easy to slip helmet on/off over them, and the adaptive volume is incredible - obviously being sat on the engine the sound is vastly different, when I'm going 70 the volume shoots up, when sat in traffic the volume drops too. They'll never replace my Sony wh-1000xm4 for use on trains or at home, but they are more than adequate for any situation where big cans aren't appropriate

Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)

ReviewText: One of my best purchases, there's not a day where I don't have these in my ears sound quality is great, there not noise cancelling but when out walking about it's better to hear a little noise the having an accident, battery last ages and notifications come up on my phone when battery is low with also playing a tone in your ear to let you know the battery is getting low, doesn't take long to fully charge the case or ear buds either

Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)
Date: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 13 July 2023
ReviewText: These buds are comfortable, even for many hours of wear.The bud batteries last 4-5 hours before needing a charge though so keep the case handy.They work well with many devices including a Pixel 6A, Steamdeck, various PCs (although mic stops working on PC after a while), but you need to manually switch between them.They're not noise cancelling so you can hear stuff around you if that's a concern (it's not for me).It's very well worth getting these if switching from wired earphones, and the freedom to work and walk around without a cable in the way is awesome!

Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)
Date: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 12 July 2023
ReviewText: Purchased some of these for myself as I had purchased some over a year ago for my son and they're still working as well as the day they came so thought I'd treat myself for a change, amazing sound, look fab, fit well and a choice of colours, battery changes quickly and lasts for ages, highly recommend.

ReviewText: I was sceptical about buying these but for the first time in my life I thought buy the same make earphones as my smartphone. In October I chose the Google pixel 6 pro on my upgrade so chose these and we're delivered to my work address yesterday.Nothing bad at all to report . The fit is snug and the sound is almost live. For 68 quid well done Google !!I rarely write reviews (I think a handful on here) credit where it is due !

Date: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 26 February 2023
ReviewText: I had a choice between these and the Nothing Ear 1 when they first came out. Having had those for 18 months, and these dropping to a very good price (£64 at the time of purchase), I picked up a pair.I should have gone with them first time.No connection issues. Fast updates. Good enough sound quality. No noise canceling, but that's ok for me. If you have a Pixel, pick up a pair.

Product: Linsoul KZ ZSN Pro Dual Driver 1BA+1DD Hybrid Metal Earphones HiFi in-Ear Monitor with Detachable 2Pin Cable, Zin Alloy Panel (Without Mic, Black)
Date: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 22 October 2022
ReviewText: Had these as part of a good deal with the Pixel 6A. To be honest I wanted a new phone, wasn't expecting much of the buds but they are actually pretty good. First thing to note is that they are very comfortable,once you get the ear position right you almost don't know you are wearing them. Secondly they actually sound really good. Finally they don't drop out and keep a strong connection. I had these pretty much free but knowing what I know I would happily pay for them.
